341
00:20:10,550 --> 00:20:12,410
It's not easy for him. 

342
00:20:12,410 --> 00:20:15,570
You try talking to him for five minutes. 

343
00:20:15,570 --> 00:20:16,670
You'll go mad. 

344
00:20:16,670 --> 00:20:19,850
A kid like that, the parents are the problem. 

345
00:20:19,850 --> 00:20:21,770
We shouldn't blame the kid. 

346
00:20:21,770 --> 00:20:23,770
It's the parents' fault. 

347
00:20:33,580 --> 00:20:34,880
Wait for me! 

348
00:20:36,670 --> 00:20:37,750
Guys! 

349
00:20:43,480 --> 00:20:45,560
Guys! Wait for me! 

350
00:20:46,440 --> 00:20:48,130
Do you have a death wish or something? 

351
00:21:03,480 --> 00:21:04,760
You drink it. 

352
00:21:04,760 --> 00:21:06,460
I'm so sorry! 

353
00:21:15,070 --> 00:21:18,030
It won't be easy for you to get all of that by next week. 

354
00:21:18,030 --> 00:21:20,000
I'm not worried. I have you. 

355
00:21:20,000 --> 00:21:23,180
I'm an old man now. 

356
00:21:23,180 --> 00:21:25,470
Too bad your dad got hurt at a time like this. 

357
00:21:25,470 --> 00:21:28,050
I know. He's being a huge crybaby about it. 

358
00:21:30,320 --> 00:21:32,710
There they go again. 

359
00:21:35,290 --> 00:21:37,060
They look like a motorcycle gang. 

360
00:21:37,060 --> 00:21:39,310
Leave them be. They're pretty violent. 

361
00:21:39,310 --> 00:21:41,670
Even calling the police doesn't work. 

362
00:21:46,990 --> 00:21:48,440
Go easy on them! 

363
00:21:48,440 --> 00:21:49,770
Hey, you! 

364
00:21:50,290 --> 00:21:51,660
Stop that! 

365
00:21:53,800 --> 00:21:55,770
Hey, I said stop it. 

366
00:21:57,040 --> 00:21:59,330
What if I can't stop? 

367
00:22:05,880 --> 00:22:07,050
Hey. 

368
00:23:06,750 --> 00:23:08,130
What is this? 

369
00:23:08,130 --> 00:23:10,230
I got humiliated! 

370
00:23:10,230 --> 00:23:11,610
Why are my credit cards suspended? 

371
00:23:17,840 --> 00:23:19,340
You can't use them for now. 

372
00:23:19,340 --> 00:23:20,940
My company's in trouble. 

373
00:23:28,570 --> 00:23:31,870
But I'm going furniture shopping with my friends tomorrow! 

374
00:23:31,870 --> 00:23:34,100
But we just got new furniture. 

375
00:23:34,100 --> 00:23:35,920
That was two years ago! 

376
00:23:35,920 --> 00:23:37,430
Shopping's great for taking your mind off things. 

377
00:23:37,430 --> 00:23:39,200
If I can't get a new husband,
I should at least get a new bed... 

378
00:23:39,200 --> 00:23:41,000
That's enough! 

379
00:23:42,300 --> 00:23:44,180
You don't have to yell. 

380
00:23:46,920 --> 00:23:48,800
Grow up, please. 

381
00:23:48,800 --> 00:23:50,300
How can you... 

382
00:24:15,680 --> 00:24:17,450
What brings you here? 

383
00:24:17,450 --> 00:24:19,450
When was the last time you visited father? 

384
00:24:19,450 --> 00:24:21,870
Don't beat around the bush. 

385
00:24:21,870 --> 00:24:24,070
It's been a year since mom passed away. 

386
00:24:24,070 --> 00:24:26,230
If one of them passed away first, 

387
00:24:26,230 --> 00:24:28,790
you said you'd take care of the other. 

388
00:24:28,790 --> 00:24:30,970
I went to father's house last week, 

389
00:24:30,970 --> 00:24:34,820
and he's aged so much in just a year. 

390
00:24:36,160 --> 00:24:38,730
He said he should get a dog or something... 

391
00:24:38,730 --> 00:24:39,770
He's getting a dog? 

392
00:24:39,770 --> 00:24:41,350
He doesn't even like dogs, 

393
00:24:41,350 --> 00:24:43,040
so imagine how lonely he must be to say that. 

394
00:24:44,460 --> 00:24:46,580
Do they own you? 

395
00:24:46,580 --> 00:24:48,980
How can you say that? Own me? 

396
00:24:48,980 --> 00:24:51,680
My friend saw you at a barbecue restaurant. 

397
00:24:51,680 --> 00:24:54,580
You were laughing and having barbecue with your in laws! 

398
00:24:54,580 --> 00:24:56,350
I wasn't laughing. 

399
00:24:56,350 --> 00:24:59,400
How can you laugh and eat at the same time? 

400
00:24:59,400 --> 00:25:01,850
You went on vacation with your in laws. 

401
00:25:02,710 --> 00:25:05,430
Have you ever taken our parents on vacation? 

402
00:25:05,430 --> 00:25:08,010
You were always too busy for them. 

403
00:25:09,280 --> 00:25:12,220
We think we lost you. 

404
00:25:12,220 --> 00:25:15,040
I hate your wife but I hate you even more. 

405
00:25:15,040 --> 00:25:18,360
If you'd gotten your bearings straight,
this wouldn't have happened. 

406
00:25:19,400 --> 00:25:22,190
I'm sorry.
It's all my fault. 

407
00:25:22,950 --> 00:25:25,350
If you know that, fix it. 

408
00:25:25,350 --> 00:25:26,890
Take care of father. 

409
00:25:26,890 --> 00:25:28,290
I will, but... 

410
00:25:28,290 --> 00:25:29,370
But what? 

411
00:25:29,370 --> 00:25:30,540
Do you need to get your wife's permission? 

412
00:25:30,540 --> 00:25:32,230
Actually, I'm not really... 

413
00:25:32,230 --> 00:25:34,090
You're not really what? 

414
00:25:34,090 --> 00:25:36,680
You're the richest of all four siblings. 

415
00:25:36,680 --> 00:25:40,350
The rest of us gave up everything for you. 

416
00:25:40,350 --> 00:25:44,070
When you wanted to sell father's land to expand your business,  

417
00:25:44,070 --> 00:25:46,240
we didn't object because you're the eldest. 

418
00:25:46,240 --> 00:25:51,820
I'm barely making ends meet, but if it weren't for my in laws, I would've taken father in. 

419
00:25:51,820 --> 00:25:53,670
I will take care of father. 

420
00:25:55,490 --> 00:25:58,840
You could've called instead of spending money on coming here. 

421
00:26:00,350 --> 00:26:03,840
Stop worrying about that and take father in this week. 

422
00:26:03,840 --> 00:26:06,240
If you don't, I'm going to bring him to you. 

423
00:26:06,240 --> 00:26:09,090
Mom's first memorial service is next week. 

424
00:26:09,090 --> 00:26:11,040
You do the ceremony at your house. 

425
00:26:22,800 --> 00:26:25,310
I'm so bored, I'm going nuts. 

426
00:26:26,070 --> 00:26:29,540
Nutty, nutty, nuts. 

427
00:26:30,040 --> 00:26:32,010
I'm going nuts. 

428
00:26:39,150 --> 00:26:42,430
Wang Don, come out and play! 

429
00:26:44,620 --> 00:26:48,060
Loser, come out and play. 

430
00:26:48,700 --> 00:26:50,070
Loser! 

431
00:26:51,690 --> 00:26:53,650
Loser's not home! 

432
00:26:55,790 --> 00:26:58,890
Loser? Did you call me loser? 

433
00:26:59,730 --> 00:27:02,220
Uncle, bring out the dishes... 

434
00:27:32,940 --> 00:27:35,520
- Grandmother, I'm here.
- You're late! 

435
00:27:35,520 --> 00:27:38,330
I came straight from work. 

436
00:27:44,420 --> 00:27:46,180
I can't believe my mother in law. 

437
00:27:46,180 --> 00:27:48,080
Why would she say something like that? 

438
00:27:48,080 --> 00:27:51,210
Like grandma said, it was worse than the Korean War. 

439
00:27:51,210 --> 00:27:52,450
Oh, my back. 

440
00:27:52,450 --> 00:27:54,440
Thank god it's grandfather's memorial service. 

441
00:27:55,080 --> 00:27:56,660
Why are you just standing there? 

442
00:27:56,660 --> 00:27:58,740
You came early. 

443
00:27:58,740 --> 00:28:00,970
Why don't you take a day off? 

444
00:28:00,970 --> 00:28:02,200
Mom can't do all this alone. 

445
00:28:02,200 --> 00:28:03,450
Hobak isn't a daughter in law. 

446
00:28:03,450 --> 00:28:05,220
Why would she take the day off to help? 

447
00:28:05,220 --> 00:28:07,110
You don't have a job,
so why couldn't you help? 

448
00:28:07,110 --> 00:28:08,830
Subak can't help. 

449
00:28:08,830 --> 00:28:12,810
She doesn't cook.
She'll just be in the way. 

450
00:28:12,810 --> 00:28:14,610
It's her good fortune. 

451
00:28:14,610 --> 00:28:16,010
It's all thanks to Minjung. 

452
00:28:16,010 --> 00:28:18,200
It was her fortune to have found a husband like him. 

453
00:28:18,200 --> 00:28:20,640
So get yourself a good husband. 

454
00:28:20,640 --> 00:28:23,280
Why am I talking to you?
I hate you! 

455
00:28:23,280 --> 00:28:24,940
Oh, mommy. 

456
00:28:24,940 --> 00:28:26,390
Let me go.
Get out of my sight. 

457
00:28:26,390 --> 00:28:28,960
Huh? This must be new! 

458
00:28:28,960 --> 00:28:30,960
How pretty!
Who bought you this? 

459
00:28:31,690 --> 00:28:33,350
Who do you think? 

460
00:28:33,350 --> 00:28:36,120
There's only one person who buys me clothes in this family. 

461
00:28:36,900 --> 00:28:38,780
I wonder what she does with all the money she makes... 

462
00:28:38,780 --> 00:28:40,510
Why would you pull something like that? 

463
00:28:40,510 --> 00:28:41,920
You broke mom's heart. 

464
00:28:41,920 --> 00:28:44,340
She was humiliated at the private fund meeting. 

465
00:28:44,340 --> 00:28:45,590
I'm going to become a writer. 

466
00:28:45,590 --> 00:28:48,060
Shut up! I'm not finished with you! 

467
00:28:48,880 --> 00:28:51,500
After that's done, clean the fish and steam it. 

468
00:28:51,500 --> 00:28:54,010
And season these vegetables. Hurry up. 

469
00:28:54,010 --> 00:28:56,320
Stop chatting and get back to work! 

470
00:28:56,320 --> 00:28:58,810
Your grandfather is probably starving. 

471
00:28:58,810 --> 00:29:03,650
You're all such useless girls! 

472
00:29:03,650 --> 00:29:06,680
Why couldn't you be sons? 

473
00:29:06,680 --> 00:29:08,070
Grandma! 

474
00:29:17,050 --> 00:29:18,780
They're a motorcycle gang. 

475
00:29:19,540 --> 00:29:23,040
Why would you follow around gang members? 

476
00:29:23,650 --> 00:29:25,030
They don't even want you. 

477
00:29:27,110 --> 00:29:28,560
Because I'm bored. 

478
00:29:29,340 --> 00:29:30,630
You're bored? 

479
00:29:32,190 --> 00:29:34,650
Do your parents know about this? 

480
00:29:34,650 --> 00:29:36,170
I don't think so. 

481
00:29:40,600 --> 00:29:42,140
Do you have a girlfriend? 

482
00:29:44,100 --> 00:29:45,470
You do! 

483
00:29:46,330 --> 00:29:47,860
What's your dream? 

484
00:29:49,810 --> 00:29:50,940
Dream? 

485
00:29:50,940 --> 00:29:52,730
What do you want to do? 

486
00:29:52,730 --> 00:29:54,730
What do you want to become? 

487
00:29:57,850 --> 00:30:01,140
If you can't answer in 5 seconds,
you don't have one. 

488
00:30:01,140 --> 00:30:03,650
You don't want to become a celebrity, do you? 

489
00:30:04,470 --> 00:30:07,370
I'm not a child.
What do you take me for? 

490
00:30:07,370 --> 00:30:10,050
Lots of kids want to become a star. 

491
00:30:10,050 --> 00:30:12,050
I'm not interested in stuff like that. 

492
00:30:12,050 --> 00:30:13,470
That's boring. 

493
00:30:13,470 --> 00:30:16,840
If you don't want a boring life, 
you must have a dream. 

494
00:30:16,840 --> 00:30:20,730
When you have a dream, you don't get bored. 

495
00:30:22,550 --> 00:30:24,170
You don't get bored? 

496
00:30:25,960 --> 00:30:27,930
Then I'll think about it. 

497
00:30:28,620 --> 00:30:31,980
Not something your parents want, 
but what you want. 

498
00:30:31,980 --> 00:30:34,110
Because you own your life. 

499
00:30:34,110 --> 00:30:35,630
In other words, 

500
00:30:37,010 --> 00:30:40,820
it's okay to make parents cry if it's for the sake of your dream. 

501
00:30:40,820 --> 00:30:42,510
Do you understand what I mean? 

502
00:30:48,770 --> 00:30:50,140
Start. 

503
00:30:50,140 --> 00:30:51,440
Okay. 

504
00:30:53,030 --> 00:30:55,900
But my son's missing. 

505
00:31:13,350 --> 00:31:15,460
[Rude Ugly Hag] 

506
00:31:18,890 --> 00:31:20,880
- Hello?
- I'm going to kill you! 

507
00:31:20,880 --> 00:31:22,530
How dare you? 

508
00:31:22,530 --> 00:31:24,930
You should come home before the sun goes down! 

509
00:31:24,930 --> 00:31:26,760
Do you even know what day today is? 

510
00:31:26,760 --> 00:31:29,770
You must be itching to get it! 

511
00:31:29,770 --> 00:31:32,020
I have a baseball bat right here! 

512
00:31:32,020 --> 00:31:33,490
Where are you? 

513
00:31:33,490 --> 00:31:34,920
Tell me before I beat you up. 

514
00:31:34,920 --> 00:31:36,540
Are you at an internet cafe again? 

515
00:31:36,540 --> 00:31:39,480
No, this is a Chinese restaurant. 

516
00:31:40,320 --> 00:31:42,160
Hello? 

517
00:31:42,160 --> 00:31:44,600
Isn't this Wang Daebak's mobile phone? 

518
00:31:44,600 --> 00:31:46,360
It is, but... 

519
00:31:49,770 --> 00:31:51,280
Who was that? 

520
00:31:51,280 --> 00:31:54,070
She's a rude, ugly hag. 

521
00:32:05,530 --> 00:32:08,910
